Into Plane Fuel supply at the airports in French Polynesia outside of Papeete (NTAA) are covered by complex supply chains requiring substantial advance notice.  In certain airports, fuel may only be available by drums or on a per bowser basis.  AEG requests minimum 5 days and suggests 10 days’ notice to confirm fuel supply is available and to provide estimated pricing on a forward planning basis.  In order to secure a fuel authorization, please provide dispatch@aegfuels.com your estimated arrival dates, departure dates, and exact estimated uplift volume.  Cancellation fees are subject to apply on any fuel delivery quantity below the estimated volume.

Price valid for general aviation aircraft parking on N1 / ANC DOT Customs Ramp to clear customs and/or receive tech-stop fuelings. In order to qualify for tax-free fuel in Peru, the flight must be declared to Peruvian Customs by the operator’s assigned ground handler prior to departure.  The ground handling agent should provide AEG and Repsol Into Plane the type of flight (Commercial PAX or Commercial Cargo) and the cargo manifest number (if applicable). Any adjustment in the flight plan that alters the next destination after Lima must be provided to AEG immediately.  All domestic flights will incur 18% LOCAL CHARGE and the Osigermin, OEFA, & FISE charges.  Tax exemptions are not valid for any military or government operated flights.

Pricing is valid for all international flights and certain general aviation domestic flights. This pricing may only be used for next destination domestic flights if the previous location before arriving at PVG is international (e.g. SIN-PVG-HGH) and the aircraft is operated for general aviation/business purposes.

The following information must be provided to AEG dispatch or on the AEG fuel release to secure fuel:
1) Departure Flight Number, 2) A/C Tail Number, 3) Ground Handling Agent Name

Uplift fee of 200 USD/flight applies to all ad-hoc flights.

Commercial aircraft will incur a 108 USD minimum service fee for uplift <3 MTN or 54 USD for <5 MTN.

No fuel or cancellation fee of 108 USD/flight may apply if ITP arranges a vehicle after receiving approval from operator or its authorized person, via calling, email or other means.

Operator's ground handling company must contact the fuel company for fuel truck arrangements upon arrival.

Additional fees:
Defueling Fee: 45 USD/ton
Refueling Fee: 40 USD/ton
Disposal & Storage Fee: 45 USD/ton per day
Quality Check Fee: 438 USD/time
